 References in Object Oriented Programming languages In Python, C#, Java, and other languages, references are implicit.
class MyClass: a = 4 b = 2 myInstance = MyClass() myReference = myInstance class MyClass { public int a; public int b; }; class Foo { static void main(string[] args) { MyClass myInstance = new MyClass(); myReference = myInstance; } }; In C++, you have to put the & character just after the type.\
class MyClass { public: int a; int b; }; int main() { MyClass myInstance = MyClass(); MyClass& myReference = myInstance; }
